h3. Problem Definition
When I share a search result to current user, the content will be blocked by Microsoft Exchange Server due to anti-spoofing protocol. By turning up the DEBUG level in the outgoing-mail log, the messages below is shown:


{noformat}
2015-12-01 21:19:08,885 DEBUG [] Sending mailitem To='someone@domain.com' Subject='' From='someone@domain.com' FromName='Michelle Chin (jira)' Cc='null' Bcc='null' ReplyTo='someone@domain.com' InReplyTo='null' MimeType='text/html' Encoding='UTF-8' Multipart='null' MessageId='null' anonymous    Mail Queue Service Message was sent with Message-Id <1516467641.3.1448975946048.JavaMail.MICHELLE$@Michelle>
{noformat}

The log above shows that the To-email address and From-email address are identical, hence it's blocked. However, this only happens on Microsoft Exchange Server.

h3. Suggested Solution
Please use the From address as configured for the outgoing mail handler instead of current user's email address.


h3. Workaround 
N/A

