Users can only see linked issues in project they have access to. This leads to different kinds of inefficiencies, because people don't know there are links. For example an issue is cloned and moved to another project, who will solve it, but someone else looks at the orginal issue and sees no links and decides to create another child issue in another project.

Also, from a data perspective, this behaviour is very wrong. The relationship between issues does not belong to either issue. A link belongs to both sides, So when looking at an object which the user has permissions to look at, the user can see all data in that object, outgoing links is part of that. Jira should always show outgoing links, but when you click on a link, that is the moment access control to that issue should be checked, NOT when showing links as information in an issue.

