As a user, I regularly want to filter out all items that have reached an "end state" in the workflow. Standard JIRA provides Open, In Progress, Resolved, Reopened, Closed. However, every JIRA project may define its own status values. This makes it hard to implement my requirement in a generic way. In my current environment, I should create a filter as follows:
{quote}
reporter = currentUser() AND status not in (Closed, "Completed ", Done, Resolved)
{quote}
But if now I would become member of a new project that has an end state "Archived", those issues will still appear in this filter. Hence, my suggestion to enable definition & detection if a status value corresponds to an end state or not.

